+# AGENTS.md
+
+## Cursor Cloud specific instructions
+
+### Project overview
+
+This is a static HTML/CSS/JavaScript web application (APUSH Learning Hub) with no build system, no package manager, and no external runtime dependencies. Python 3 is used only for the local dev server and CI linting.
+
+### Running the dev server
+
+```bash
+python3 test-server.py
+```
+
+Serves the app at `http://localhost:8000/index.html` on port 8000. The server script auto-opens a browser — in headless/CI environments this is harmless (it will fail silently).
+
+### Linting
+
+The CI workflow (`.github/workflows/python-app.yml`) runs `flake8` on the Python files. To replicate locally:
+
+```bash
+flake8 . --count --select=E9,F63,F7,F82 --show-source --statistics
+flake8 . --count --exit-zero --max-complexity=10 --max-line-length=127 --statistics
+```
+
+There is no JavaScript linter configured in the repo.
+
+### Testing
+
+The CI runs `pytest`, but no Python tests exist yet — the suite collects 0 items and exits clean.
+
+### Key gotchas
+
+- There is **no `package.json`**, **no `requirements.txt`**, and **no build step**. Do not try to run `npm install` or `pip install -r requirements.txt`.
+- All data persistence is via browser `localStorage`. Clearing it resets all progress.
+- The Gemini AI integration is **optional** and requires a user-provided API key; the app gracefully falls back to sample questions without one.
+- `flake8` and `pytest` are installed via `pip install flake8 pytest` (they are not pinned in a requirements file).
